==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
From {{och-l|辧}}, a {{Han compound|辡|刀|c1=p|c2=s|t2=knife|ls=psc|nocap=1}}. However, the phonetic component (the reduplication of the knife to mark prisoners) perhaps symbolizes two prisoners accusing each other, hence two different versions, which then leads to the concept of "discriminate".

===Etymology===
Cognate with {{och-l|辯}}. {{och-l|辨|id=2|divide, distinguish, discriminate, dispute}} and its two [[exopassive]] derivatives {{och-l|釆|{{lit|(to cause to be) divided}} > discriminate, distinguish}} and {{och-l|瓣|{{lit|what is divided}} > piece, section, segment}} belong to the same word-family, which may be related to either {{och-l|班|to distribute → to arrange, classify → class, group}} or {{cog|lus|pʰel||to split, cut in halves}} (with medial *{{IPAfont|-r-}} dropped after labial initials according to Mizo phonotactics) ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

